"title": "3290: Holy Spirit, the life-giver",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "3290: holy spirit, the life-giver",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Through the Holy Spirit, God gives birth to and supports both natural and spiritual life. For this reason, Scripture likens the Holy Spirit to life-giving water.</p>\n<h2>The creating Spirit (or breath) of God gives and sustains life</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen1:2\">GEN 1:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen2:7\">GEN 2:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job26:13\">JOB 26:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job27:3\">JOB 27:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job32:8\">JOB 32:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job33:4\">JOB 33:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job34:14\">JOB 34:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps33:6\">PSA 33:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps104:30\">PSA 104:30</a></p>\n<h2>The Holy Spirit gives new life</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek37:1-Ezek37:14\">EZK 37:1–37:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek36:26-Ezek36:28\">EZK 36:26–36:28</a></p>\n<h2>The Holy Spirit is the life-giver in the conception of Jesus Christ</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt1:18\">MAT 1:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt1:20\">MAT 1:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:35\">LUK 1:35</a></p>\n<h2>The Holy Spirit gives resurrection life to Jesus Christ</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet3:18\">1PE 3:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:4\">ROM 1:4</a></p>\n<h2>The Holy Spirit brings new spiritual life</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John3:5\">JHN 3:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John3:6\">JHN 3:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John3:8\">JHN 3:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John6:63\">JHN 6:63</a></p>\n<h3>The Spirit sets believers free from bondage to works that lead to death</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:2\">ROM 8:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:6\">ROM 8:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:13\">ROM 8:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal6:8\">GAL 6:8</a></p>\n<h2>The Holy Spirit is described as life-giving water</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John7:37-John7:39\">JHN 7:37–7:39</a></strong> <em>Words spoken by Jesus Christ at the Feast of Tabernacles.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa32:15\">ISA 32:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa44:3-Isa44:4\">ISA 44:3–44:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek36:25-Ezek36:27\">EZK 36:25–36:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek39:29\">EZK 39:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek47:1-Ezek47:12\">EZK 47:1–47:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech14:8\">ZEC 14:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John4:10\">JHN 4:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John4:14\">JHN 4:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev22:1-Rev22:2\">REV 22:1–22:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev22:17\">REV 22:17</a></p>",
